◦
AI Agents are autonomous software programs designed to perform specific tasks. They are modular systems for task-specific automation, often driven by LLMs and LIMs. Their operational scope is enabled by integrating LLMs and LIMs as core reasoning modules.
◦
Agentic AI systems are a paradigm shift representing systems of multiple AI agents collaborating to achieve complex goals. They manage multi-step, complex tasks and systems. They represent a conceptual leap from isolated systems to orchestrated multi-agent architectures.
